---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/museum.css";
---

<Layout
  title="OmeletYouFinish.com | Museum of Dumb Ideas"
  description="The story of an omelet-themed travel blog that ended shortly after the domain was purchased."
>
  <div class="museum-page">
    <p class="museum-back">
      <a href="/museum/">← Museum of Dumb Ideas</a>
    </p>

    <header class="exhibit-header">
      <p class="exhibit-number">Accession No. MDI-0001</p>
      <h1>OmeletYouFinish.com</h1>

      <p class="museum-subtitle">
        Imma let you finish, but this may be one of the greatest unused domains
        of all time.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="museum-plaque" aria-label="Exhibit information">
      <p class="plaque-label">Exhibit Information</p>

      <dl>
        <dt>Classification</dt>
        <dd>Purchased Domain</dd>

        <dt>Original Concept</dt>
        <dd>Omelet-themed travel blog</dd>

        <dt>Current Status</dt>
        <dd>Retired before construction</dd>

        <dt>Primary Artifact</dt>
        <dd>One completely legitimate domain registration</dd>

        <dt>Cause of Failure</dt>
        <dd>Five additional minutes of thought</dd>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <article class="exhibit-body">
      <h2>Description</h2>

      <p>
        OmeletYouFinish.com began with a simple observation: people enjoy
        breakfast, people enjoy travel, and the internet had somehow failed to
        combine those interests with a Kanye West reference.
      </p>

      <p>
        The proposed site would document omelets encountered while traveling.
        Each breakfast would become a destination, each restaurant a cultural
        experience, and each plate of eggs another opportunity to justify
        purchasing the domain.
      </p>

      <p>
        The domain was secured. The concept was preserved. Development,
        fortunately, did not begin.
      </p>

      <h2>Original Hypothesis</h2>

      <blockquote>
        People love breakfast. People love travel. This obviously combines
        both.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>What Went Wrong</h2>

      <p>
        Nothing technically went wrong. The idea simply encountered the rare
        but effective project-management technique known as thinking about it
        again.
      </p>

      <p>
        Further review determined that maintaining an international omelet
        database might require more breakfast travel than the available budget
        could support.
      </p>

      <h2>Artifacts</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>The registered domain name.</li>
        <li>The original omelet travel-blog concept.</li>
        <li>A joke that remained funny longer than the business plan.</li>
        <li>This exhibit, which technically means the domain eventually produced something.</li>
      </ul>

      <aside class="curator-note">
        <h2>Curator's Note</h2>

        <p>
          Sometimes buying the domain is enough.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <h2>Exhibit Rating</h2>

      <div class="rating-grid">
        <article class="rating-card">
          <h3>Originality</h3>
          <p class="rating-value" aria-label="Five out of five stars">
            ★★★★★
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rating-card">
          <h3>Practicality</h3>
          <p class="rating-value" aria-label="One out of five stars">
            ★☆☆☆☆
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rating-card">
          <h3>Financial Damage</h3>
          <p class="rating-value" aria-label="One out of five stars">
            ★☆☆☆☆
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rating-card">
          <h3>Storytelling Value</h3>
          <p class="rating-value" aria-label="Five out of five stars">
            ★★★★★
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Domains are cheaper than fully developed bad ideas.</li>
        <li>Not every joke deserves a production server.</li>
        <li>A failed project can still become a successful story.</li>
      </ul>

      <footer class="museum-footer">
        <p>
          OmeletYouFinish.com is on permanent loan from the Archives of
          Questionable Decisions.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/museum/">Continue through the Museum</a>
          ·
          <a href="/">Return to BradCooke.com</a>
        </p>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
